cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.MA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on proposing a PHY/MAC layer design for CDMA based communication for low power IoT devices, which falls under the networking and internet architecture sub-category.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the optimization of the CDMA access for IoT devices, which involves information theory concepts such as channel coding and modulation schemes.
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper proposes a coexisting operation of CDMA based IoT network in presence of the existing LTE network, which falls under the communications and networking sub-category.
4. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The proposed design involves integrating IoT traffic with legacy systems, which can be considered as a multi-agent system.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the implementation of the proposed design using Software Defined Radios, which involves systems and control concepts.
